objectives.name: Primary Efficacy Objective
objectives.text: To demonstrate that QW LY3298176 10 mg and/or 15 mg is noninferior to insulin glargine for change from baseline in HbA1c at 52 weeks

objectives.name: Key Secondary Efficacy Objective 1
objectives.text: To demonstrate that QW LY3298176 5 mg is noninferior to insulin glargine for change from baseline in HbA1c at 52 weeks

objectives.name: Key Secondary Efficacy Objective 2
objectives.text: To demonstrate that QW LY3298176 5 mg, 10 mg, and/or 15 mg is superior to insulin glargine for change from baseline in weight at 52 weeks

objectives.name: Key Secondary Efficacy Objective 3
objectives.text: To demonstrate that QW LY3298176 5 mg, 10 mg, and/or 15 mg is superior to insulin glargine for change from baseline in HbA1c at 52 weeks

objectives.name: Key Secondary Efficacy Objective 4
objectives.text: To demonstrate that QW LY3298176 5 mg, 10 mg, and/or 15 mg is superior to insulin glargine for the proportion of patients with HbA1c target values of <7.0% (53 mmol/mol) at 52 weeks

objectives.name: Additional Secondary Efficacy Objective
objectives.text: To demonstrate that QW LY3298176 5 mg, 10 mg, and/or 15 mg is superior to insulin glargine at 52 weeks

objectives.name: Secondary Safety Objective
objectives.text: To compare the safety of LY3298176 5 mg, 10 mg, and 15 mg LY3298176 to insulin glargine at 52 weeks and at the end of the safety follow-up period

objectives.name: Secondary Pharmacokinetics Objective
objectives.text: To characterize the pharmacokinetics (PK) of LY3298176 5 mg, 10 mg, and 15 mg and evaluate the relationships between LY3298176 exposure and safety, tolerability, and efficacy measures

objectives.name: Exploratory Glycemic Objective
objectives.text: To characterize long-term glycemic control with LY3298176 5 mg, 10 mg, and 15 mg

objectives.name: Exploratory Comparison Objective
objectives.text: To compare LY3298176 5 mg, 10 mg, and 15 mg to insulin glargine with respect to lipids, BMI, waist circumference, biomarkers, and PROs

endpoints.text: Mean change in 7-point self-monitored blood glucose profiles from baseline

endpoints.text: Proportion of patients who achieved weight loss of ≥5%, >10%, and >15% from baseline

endpoints.text: Treatment-emergent adverse events (TEAEs)

endpoints.text: Early discontinuations of study drug due to adverse events (AEs)

endpoints.text: Adjudicated deaths and nonfatal major CV events

endpoints.text: Adjudicated pancreatic AEs

endpoints.name: Thyroid/Calcitonin Endpoint
endpoints.text: Medullary thyroid carcinoma (MTC), C-cell hyperplasia, and serum calcitonin

endpoints.name: Immunogenicity Endpoint
endpoints.text: Incidence of treatment-emergent LY3298176 anti-drug antibodies and systemic hypersensitivity reactions

endpoints.text: Mean change in systolic and diastolic blood pressure and heart rate from baseline

endpoints.text: Occurrence of hypoglycemic events

endpoints.text: Changes from baseline in mean body mass index (BMI)

endpoints.text: Change in waist circumference

endpoints.name: Exploratory Biomarkers Endpoint
endpoints.text: Biomarkers

endpoints.name: PROs Endpoint
endpoints.text: Patient-Reported Outcomes (European Quality of Life – dimensions [EQ-5D-5L], Ability to Perform Physical Activities of Daily Living [APPADL], Impact of Weight on Self-Perception [IW-SP], status (s) and change (c) versions of Diabetes Treatment Satisfaction Questionnaire (DTSQ)
